OpenSCAD Polygon Editor
=======================

A web-based visual editor for OpenSCAD `polygon([...])` data. Paste your
OpenSCAD code, drag points around, and the source updates live.

OpenSCAD itself is a scripted CAD tool: http://www.openscad.org/

Original project: https://github.com/daid/OpenSCAD-polygon-editor

Usage
-----
Open `index.html` in any modern browser. No build step or server needed.

Tools
-----
- Edit (E)   — Select and drag points. Click again on a smooth point's
               control points to drag handles.
- Add  (A)   — Click on the grid to append a point to the current path.
- Rem  (R)   — Click a point to delete it.
- Image (I)  — Load an image to trace over (URL or local file).

Path-point types (with Edit tool active):
- Corner — straight segments between neighbors.
- Smooth — Bezier control points that you can drag.

Features
--------
- Undo / redo                       (Ctrl/Cmd+Z, Ctrl+Y or Ctrl+Shift+Z)
- Zoom                              (Ctrl/Cmd+wheel, +/- keys, 0 to reset)
- Snap to grid toggle
- Adjustable grid size
- Keyboard delete for selected point (Del / Backspace)
- Copy code to clipboard
- Clear all paths
- Dark / light theme toggle (persisted)
- Live SVG drawing area, responsive to window resize
- Trace image overlay (URL or local file)

3D Preview
----------
Toggle "Enable 3D" in the toolbox to open a live 3D viewport beside the 2D
editor. The current polygons are extruded into solid geometry and rendered
with Three.js + OrbitControls (drag to orbit, scroll to zoom, right-drag to
pan).

Two extrusion modes:
- Linear extrude — height + optional twist (deg) and end-scale.
- Rotate extrude — sweep around the Z axis with adjustable segments and
  angle (matches OpenSCAD's `rotate_extrude`).

"Copy 3D" copies generated `linear_extrude(...) polygon([...])` or
`rotate_extrude(...) polygon([...])` code, ready to paste into OpenSCAD.

Dependencies
------------
- Raphael 2.3.0 — CDN, for 2D SVG.
- Three.js 0.160 + OrbitControls — CDN ES modules via importmap, for 3D.
- No jQuery; everything else is vanilla JS / standard browser APIs.

File overview
-------------
- index.html — page layout
- style.css  — modern theme (CSS variables, light/dark)
- osped.js   — 2D polygon editor logic + OspedAPI bridge
- three3d.js — 3D viewport (ES module)
